{"action": "input", "code": "def split_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[np.ndarray, np.ndarray]:\n    sub1 = input_grid[:, :3]\n    sub2 = input_grid[:, 3:]\n    return (sub1, sub2)\ndef create_sub1_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    sub1 = input_grid[:, :3]\n    return sub1\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    sub1, sub2 = split_grid(input_grid)\n    new = create_sub1_grid(sub1)\n    copy = copy_non_black_pixels(sub1, sub2, new)\n    out = turn_non_black_to_pink(copy)\n    return out\ndef copy_non_black_pixels(sub1: np.ndarray, sub2: np.ndarray, new: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    mask = sub2 != black\n    new[mask] = sub2[mask]\n    return new\ndef turn_non_black_to_pink(copy: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    copy[copy != black] = pink\n    return copy", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    sub1, sub2 = `split the 3x6 input_grid into two 3x3 grid`(input_grid)\n    new = `creat a grid same as sub1`(sub1)\n    copy = `copy the not black pixels in sub2 to new at the same position`(sub1, sub2, new)\n    out = `turn all not black pixels in copy to pink`(copy)\n    return out", "gpt_code": "def split_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[np.ndarray, np.ndarray]:\n    sub1 = input_grid[:, :3]\n    sub2 = input_grid[:, 3:]\n    return (sub1, sub2)\ndef create_sub1_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    sub1 = input_grid[:, :3]\n    return sub1\ndef copy_non_black_pixels(sub1: np.ndarray, sub2: np.ndarray, new: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    mask = sub2 != black\n    new[mask] = sub2[mask]\n    return new\ndef turn_non_black_to_pink(copy: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    copy[copy != black] = pink\n    return copy", "holes": {"split_grid": "split the 3x6 input_grid into two 3x3 grid", "create_sub1_grid": "creat a grid same as sub1", "copy_non_black_pixels": "copy the not black pixels in sub2 to new at the same position", "turn_non_black_to_pink": "turn all not black pixels in copy to pink"}}
